   --> [MOD] localization\replace\english\RICE_sri_lanka_l_english.yml
471 |  game_concept_mahavihara_desc:0 "The Mahavihara, alongside the [abhayagiri|E] and [jetavana|E], are one of the three major [RICE_sri_lanka_monasteries|E] in the [RICE_sri_lanka_struggle|E], or its Buddhist community. In-game, the Mahavihara are represented by an orange icon: @RICE_mahavihara_icon!.\n\nYou can raise or lower the [RICE_sri_lanka_prominence|E] of the Mahavihara through different [decisions|E], [activities|E], and so on, especially if you have the [GetTrait('RICE_mahavihara_trait').GetName( GetNullCharacter )] [trait|E], which can be gained by taking the [decision|E] to $RICE_sri_lanka_choose_monastic_sect$. Keep this in mind if you wish to end the [struggle|E] in [RICE_sri_lanka_short|E].\n\nHistorically, the Mahavihara were the more 'traditionalist' monastery or sect of ancient and medieval Sri Lankan Buddhism. They were typically skeptical or dismissive of what they saw as heterodox ideas from India. According to traditional chronicles, they were the ones who "won" out in the end against the other monasteries."
    |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ 

error(missing-item): trait RICE_abhayagiri_trait not defined in common/traits/
   --> [MOD] localization\replace\english\RICE_sri_lanka_l_english.yml
474 |  game_concept_abhayagiri_desc:0 "The Abhayagiri, alongside the [mahavihara|E] and [jetavana|E], are one of the three major [RICE_sri_lanka_monasteries|E] in the [RICE_sri_lanka_struggle|E], or its Buddhist community. In-game, the Abhayagiri are represented by an yellow icon: @RICE_abhayagiri_icon!.\n\nYou can raise or lower the [RICE_sri_lanka_prominence|E] of the Abhayagiri through different [decisions|E], [activities|E], and so on, especially if you have the [GetTrait('RICE_abhayagiri_trait').GetName( GetNullCharacter )] [trait|E], which can be gained by taking the [decision|E] to $RICE_sri_lanka_choose_monastic_sect$. Keep this in mind if you wish to end the [struggle|E] in [RICE_sri_lanka_short|E].\n\nHistorically, the Abhayagiri were the more innovative monastery or sect of ancient and medieval Sri Lankan Buddhism. They often incorporated ideas from the Mahayana and Vajrayana varieties of Buddhism into the Theravada form of Buddhism practiced on Sri Lanka. At one point, they were the largest major monastery on the island."
    |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ 

error(missing-item): trait RICE_jetavana_trait not defined in common/traits/
   --> [MOD] localization\replace\english\RICE_sri_lanka_l_english.yml
477 |  game_concept_jetavana_desc:0 "The Jetavana, alongside the [mahavihara|E] and [abhayagiri|E], are one of the three major [RICE_sri_lanka_monasteries|E] in the [RICE_sri_lanka_struggle|E], or its Buddhist community. In-game, the Jetavana are represented by an maroon icon: @RICE_jetavana_icon!.\n\nYou can raise or lower the [RICE_sri_lanka_prominence|E] of the Jetavana through different [decisions|E], [activities|E], and so on, and so on, especially if you have the [GetTrait('RICE_jetavana_trait').GetName( GetNullCharacter )] [trait|E], which can be gained by taking the [decision|E] to $RICE_sri_lanka_choose_monastic_sect$. Keep this in mind if you wish to end the [struggle|E] in [RICE_sri_lanka_short|E].\n\nHistorically, the Jetavana were open to ideas from Mahayana and Vajrayana Buddhism, similarly to the [abhayagiri|E]. They were the smallest and usually least influential of the three sects. However, the main stupa at the site of their main monastery is home to a great stupa, an often mound-shaped Buddhist monument, called the #italic Jetavanaramaya#!, which at one point was the tallest building in the world after the pyramids."
    |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ 

