257 |  RICE_sri_lanka_pali_literature_kavya_legends_desc:0 "$RICE_sri_lanka_pali_literature_basic$This text is a #italic kavya#!, a form of Sanskrit courtly poetry originally from mainland India, but adapted to the Pali language. Despite its sensual style, this poem uses such worldly aesthetics to inspire its Buddhist audience to greater religious devotion, such as by explaining the merits of spiritual practice or leading a virtuous life, or recounting a Buddhist legend of a famous figure like the Buddha, some Bodhisattva or enlightened being, or a historical monk."
