329 |  struggle_RICE_sri_lanka_phase_degeneration_desc:0 "The Buddha's teachings – and the [RICE_sri_lanka_sangha|E] itself – are in decline in Sri Lanka. Perhaps attempts to purge the [RICE_sri_lanka_monasteries|E] of immoral, undisciplined monastics during the [struggle_phase_sri_lanka_purification|E] failed. Or, perhaps the wealth and influence of the [RICE_sri_lanka_monasteries|E] during the [struggle_phase_sri_lanka_accumulation|E] attracted military raids by rapacious foreign heathens, or confiscation by unscrupulus, greedy local elites.\n\nHowever, as the Buddha taught, good #italic and#! bad things are impermanent. From the darkness of the degenerate era, a brighter future might blossom in a [struggle_phase_sri_lanka_purification|E], as righteous monastics, scholars, and leaders cleanse the [RICE_sri_lanka_sangha|E] of corruption and wrongdoers. Alternatively, local elites might pool together enough resources to revive the [RICE_sri_lanka_monasteries|E] in the [struggle_phase_sri_lanka_accumulation|E], bringing about a new era of prosperity on the island."
    |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ 

