331 |  struggle_RICE_sri_lanka_phase_accumulation_desc:0 "The [RICE_sri_lanka_struggle|E] accumulates power and influence influence, thanks to the support from both elites and commoners, who in turn accumulate good merit. Perhaps the [struggle_phase_sri_lanka_purification|E] resulted in greater respect towards the [RICE_sri_lanka_monasteries|E] by laypeople, or, perhaps the strife and chaos of the [struggle_phase_sri_lanka_degeneration|E] encouraged laypeople to support the [RICE_sri_lanka_monasteries|E].\n\nThe growth of the [RICE_sri_lanka_monasteries|E], however, is a double edged sword. Monastics might grow complacent and lazy requiring a [struggle_phase_sri_lanka_purification|E] to rid the [RICE_sri_lanka_sangha|E] of heretical ideas and immorality. Even worse, the island might attract greedy scoundrels, both foreign heathens and local rulers, who seek to plunder the [RICE_sri_lanka_monasteries|E] and destroy the [RICE_sri_lanka_sangha|E], and the monastics are too corrupt to inspire the people, leading to the [struggle_phase_sri_lanka_degeneration|E]. "
    |                                                          ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ 

