479 |  game_concept_RICE_sri_lanka_prominence_desc:0 "Prominence are three global values representing the influence and esteem of the three most powerful [RICE_sri_lanka_monasteries|E] in the [RICE_sri_lanka_struggle|E], or Buddhist community, namely the [mahavihara_i|E] [mahavihara|E], [abhayagiri_i|E] [abhayagiri|E], and [jetavana_i|E] [jetavana|E].\n\nThese values play an important role in the [struggle|E] in [RICE_sri_lanka_short|E], as getting them to reach a certain amount is required to end the [struggle|E]. Prominence can be increased or decreased through various [decisions|E], [activities|E], events, and more; oftentimes, this impact is greater if you are have the patron [trait|E] of one of the three monasteries. This [trait|E] can be acquired by taking the [decision|E] to $RICE_sri_lanka_choose_monastic_sect$.\n\nAnother perk of keeping your patronized monastery's prominence high is that it gives you a small, randomized amount of [piety_i|E] [piety|E] and [prestige_i|E] [prestige|E] every year; how much depends on your monastery's prominence level."
    |                                                                                                                                                      ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ 

