1028 |  sri_lanka.0006.desc:0 "After centuries of disunity and conflict within the [buddhism.GetAdjective] community of [GetGeographicalRegion('RICE_sri_lanka_alt_region').GetName], the various monasteries of the island have agreed to reunite under my auspices and that of the [GetPlayer.Custom('RICE_sri_lanka_patronized_monastery')] monastery which I patronize.\n\nWe now need a symbol for the Sangha to rally around. Some in the monastic community have claimed that one of the island’s most revered religious relics was destined to become such a symbol. The religious rituals surrounding this relic should be glorified, they say, to honor the Buddha, exemplify the Dharma, and inspire the newly united Sangha.\n\nThe question, now, is which relic was actually destined to fulfill such a role?"
     |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ 

warning(missing-item): custom localization RICE_sri_lanka_patronized_monastery not defined in common/customizable_localization/
    --> [MOD] localization\replace\english\RICE_sri_lanka_l_english.yml
1040 |  sri_lanka.0008.desc:0 "$sri_lanka.0005.desc.intro$It took the efforts of a [sri_lanka_struggle_ender.GetFaith.GetAdjective] [sri_lanka_struggle_ender.GetTitleAsNameNoTooltip] by the name of [sri_lanka_struggle_ender.GetFirstName], however, to see to it that the teachings of the Buddha could flower again – not in [GetGeographicalRegion('RICE_sri_lanka_alt_region').GetName], but in [sri_lanka_struggle_ender.GetPrimaryTitle.GetName].\n\n[sri_lanka_struggle_ender.GetFirstNameNoTooltip] has achieved this through a powerful alliance with the most prominent monastery on the island, the #bold [sri_lanka_struggle_ender.Custom('RICE_sri_lanka_patronized_monastery')]#!, which [sri_lanka_struggle_ender.GetSheHe] has patronized extensively. With the Sangha revived, it is clear that the center of [buddhism.GetNameNoTooltip] – at least among those who follow the [GetFaithDoctrine('rice_theravada_canon_doctrine').GetBaseNameNoTooltip] – has thus been reestablished elsewhere: [sri_lanka_struggle_ender.GetPrimaryTitle.GetNameNoTooltip], from now on, is a new holy land for [buddhism.GetNameNoTooltip]."
     |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ 

warning(missing-item): custom localization RICE_sri_lanka_patronized_monastery not defined in common/customizable_localization/
    --> [MOD] localization\replace\english\RICE_sri_lanka_l_english.yml
1090 |  sri_lanka.0019.desc:0 "I have actively done my part to support the [ROOT.Char.GetFaith.GetReligion.GetAdjective] #italic Sangha#! of [GetGeographicalRegion('RICE_sri_lanka_alt_region').GetName]. However, the relatively small numbers of [ROOT.Char.GetCulture.GetName] [ROOT.Char.GetFaith.GetAdjective] monastics on the island had been a hurdle in developing my relationship with the island's religious establishment, particularly the [GetPlayer.Custom('RICE_sri_lanka_patronized_monastery')] who I patronize.\n\nI am working with the [GetPlayer.Custom('RICE_sri_lanka_patronized_monastery')] to have more [ROOT.Char.GetCulture.GetNameNoTooltip] [ROOT.Char.GetFaith.GetAdjectiveNoTooltip] monastics in [GetGeographicalRegion('RICE_sri_lanka_alt_region').GetName], whether we ordain [ROOT.Char.GetCulture.GetCollectiveNounNoTooltip] living here who desire to become [ROOT.Char.GetFaith.GetAdjectiveNoTooltip] monastics, bring in such monastics from abroad, or both. In doing so, I hope we may be even more involved in the island's #italic Sangha#!.\n\nWhile there will undoubtedly be some tensions at first as these new monastics are integrated into the existing community, I am sure in the long run, this will only strengthen the foundations of [ROOT.Char.GetFaith.GetReligion.GetNameNoTooltip] in [GetGeographicalRegion('RICE_sri_lanka_alt_region').GetNameNoTooltip]."
     |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ 

