1299 |  sri_lanka.0071.desc:0 "At last, I have reached [GetPlayer.Custom('RICE_sri_pada')]. The mountain itself towers high above me at a distance, surrounded by a seemingly endless canopy of greenest trees. It looks daunting, yet I have already walked all the way here. There is no turning back!\n\nFor now, however, I and my entourage will need to recoup our energy. The way upwards will be difficult, so we need to have well-rested bodies and minds if we are to make our way to the peak.\n\nWe make our way through crowds of fellow pilgrims – some fellow [ROOT.Char.GetFaith.GetAdherentNamePlural], others followers of other creeds – as we prepare to rest for the night. It is remarkable how people of all faiths venerate this mountain, and even more remarkable that they maintain relative peace with each other."
     |                                                                    ^^^^^^^^^^^^^ 

warning(missing-item): custom localization RICE_sri_pada not defined in common/customizable_localization/
    --> [MOD] localization\replace\english\RICE_sri_lanka_l_english.yml
1303 |  sri_lanka.0072.desc:0 "We have started our trek up [GetPlayer.Custom('RICE_sri_pada')]. There are two main routes going to the main peak.\n\nOne, which some call the #italic Mama#! track, is a relatively easy, gentle walk, so anyone who climbs up the mountain this way is not considered a true pilgrim. The other route, called the #italic Baba#! track, is much harder, and it is the route we currently are on.\n\nAlong the route, there are a number of chains going up the stairs, to help pilgrims up the steps. I am not even partway through, and I already feel exhausted!"
     |                                                                        ^^^^^^^^^^^^^ 

warning(missing-item): custom localization RICE_sri_pada not defined in common/customizable_localization/
    --> [MOD] localization\replace\english\RICE_sri_lanka_l_english.yml
1307 |  sri_lanka.0073.desc:0 "At last, I have reached the peak of [GetPlayer.Custom('RICE_sri_pada')] – and what a magnificent view! Against the pure blue sky, one mostly sees pure white clouds surrounding the mountain when gazing downwards, interspersed with the ever-green canopy of trees, all of which obscures the base.\n\nBut I am not here to admire the scenery. I hurry my way across the summit to where most of the other pilgrims congregate: a footprint spanning a miraculously large length on a lofty black rock.\n\nAt last, before my eyes, is the very footprint that [GetPlayer.Custom('RICE_sri_pada_footprint_person')] made so long ago. We will spend a few days in prayer before we return, but before we do so, it is customary for [ROOT.Char.GetFaith.GetAdherentNamePlural] like myself to donate some gold and precious items"
     |                                                                                ^^^^^^^^^^^^^ 

warning(missing-item): custom localization RICE_sri_pada_footprint_person not defined in common/customizable_localization/
    --> [MOD] localization\replace\english\RICE_sri_lanka_l_english.yml
1307 |  sri_lanka.0073.desc:0 "At last, I have reached the peak of [GetPlayer.Custom('RICE_sri_pada')] – and what a magnificent view! Against the pure blue sky, one mostly sees pure white clouds surrounding the mountain when gazing downwards, interspersed with the ever-green canopy of trees, all of which obscures the base.\n\nBut I am not here to admire the scenery. I hurry my way across the summit to where most of the other pilgrims congregate: a footprint spanning a miraculously large length on a lofty black rock.\n\nAt last, before my eyes, is the very footprint that [GetPlayer.Custom('RICE_sri_pada_footprint_person')] made so long ago. We will spend a few days in prayer before we return, but before we do so, it is customary for [ROOT.Char.GetFaith.GetAdherentNamePlural] like myself to donate some gold and precious items"
     |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ 

warning(missing-item): custom localization RICE_sri_pada not defined in common/customizable_localization/
    --> [MOD] localization\replace\english\RICE_sri_lanka_l_english.yml
1313 |  sri_lanka.0074.desc:0 "After spending days in prayer, we start to make our way down the #italic Mama#! track of [GetPlayer.Custom('RICE_sri_pada')]. This route may have been easier than the way going up, but it is still a strenuous trek downwards, and by the time we have reached the bottom of the mountain, I and my entourage are exhausted.\n\nAs we catch our breath, I make note of the famous ancient tree at the base of the mountain. People say this tree is of supernatural quality, for its leaves never fall, and some hermits even claim eating the leaves will regain their youth. Regardless of the truth of the matter, it is a beautiful tree, one clearly old and wise, and a wonderful sight to end our trip on."
     |                                                                                                                                     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^ 

warning(missing-item): custom localization RICE_sri_pada not defined in common/customizable_localization/
    --> [MOD] localization\replace\english\RICE_sri_lanka_l_english.yml
1331 |  sri_lanka.0080.desc:0 "One of the most fascinating things about [GetPlayer.Custom('RICE_sri_pada')] that I notice more and more, now that I am here, is that the site is honored by followers of many different creeds, not just [ROOT.Char.GetFaith.GetAdherentNamePlural].\n\nFor instance, there are followers of other faiths who call the mountain [GetPlayer.Custom('RICE_sri_pada_opp')], instead of [GetPlayer.Custom('RICE_sri_pada')] as we do. Not everyone believes [GetPlayer.Custom('RICE_sri_pada_footprint_person')] made the footprint at the mountain’s peak either.\n\nDespite this, and despite the fact there are still plenty of tensions between the various groups here, it is fascinating if not inspiring for some to see so people of many beliefs, including those who would normally be at blows with each other, share this sacred space."
     |                                                                                     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^ 

