1560 |  sri_lanka.0150.pattini_games_intro:0 "In [GetGeographicalRegion('RICE_sri_lanka_alt_region').GetName], it is the traditional custom for villages to host ritual games for the goddess [GetPlayer.Custom('RICE_pattini')] on special occasions.\n\nBoth teams for these games are typically male, and these are great occasions for the men to show off. One team represents the goddess, while another team represents her spouse, or some male deity. If the goddess’ team wins, this surely ensures good agricultural fertility and prosperity for the year, but both teams are expected to play seriously for the ritual to be considered legitimate.\n\n"
     |                                                                                                                                                                                                           ^^^^^^^^^^^^ 

