1567 |  sri_lanka.0151.desc:0 "$sri_lanka.0150.pattini_games_intro$I heard that the coconut game, #italic porakeliya#!, was recently played in a prominent village in [county.GetNameNoTier]. Both teams have individual team members face off at a time, and the two players hurl coconuts at each other at the same time, trying to crack the coconut of the other person. The team who cracks the most coconuts of the other team wins. It is a dangerous but exciting game!"
