482 |  socotra.0031.desc:0 "Years of abuse at the hands of corrupt officials and unjust laws have caused much unrest among the Muslims of Socotra. Their chief representative is [RICE_socotra_zahra_character.GetTitledFirstName], a poet of some renown. Today, she is airing their grievances with me.\n\n“All we ask for is fair and just treatment, [ROOT.Char.GetTitleAsNameNoTooltip] [ROOT.Char.GetFirstNameNoTooltip],” she says. “Please consider relaxing the restrictions and unjust laws placed on us, and look into the unrighteous actions some officials have done to besmirch your good name.”\n\nHer eloquent demands come off more as a friendly request, even if there is the implicit threat of further unrest. I have heard she plans to send word to other Muslim rulers to ask for their aid if I refuse her demands, so I must tread carefully."
