1814 |  tarim_basin.0243.desc:0 "Long ago, the [RICE_tarim_basin_fake_china_person.GetDynasty.GetName] clan claimed to be rulers of China… from a certain point of view. They felt justified in doing so as they ruled over parts of the [GetGeographicalRegion('world_steppe_tarim').GetName], which many Muslims of the era consider to be part of the former dominions of China. Perhaps it is more correct to say they were rulers #italic in#! a part of China.\n\nNow, there is nothing left to support the charade. Due to one reason or another, the scions of the [RICE_tarim_basin_fake_china_person.GetDynasty.GetName] clan have lost control of their territories in the Tarim Basin. For them to be considered Sultans or Khans of China is laughable, and no one would take such claims seriously anymore."
