444 |  yazidi.0060.desc:0 "Lately, I’ve been gathering the resources needed to make a great sacrifice of a bull.\n\nIn our traditional [faith.GetAdjective] cosmology, at the dawn of time, the great god Mithra sacrificed the primordial bull. Before that, the cosmos initially created by [faith.CreatorGodName] was lacking in life and everything was still; it was thus Mithra’s sacrifice of the bull that allowed the second stage of creation to initiate.\n\nThere are some in other regions who believe this first sacrifice was an evil act, performed by evil beings, including those who we share a great number of religious beliefs and customs with. However, we disagree: the sacrifice was necessary and a good act. Thus, we seek to re-enact the original bull sacrifice ourselves through this religious ritual."
